ange (~40% expansion vs. ~320% for SC). The key limitation is that high LiTFSI concentration causes corrosion of the NCM811 cathode, leading to severe capacity degradation in full cells.","must_include":["anion-dominated solvation structure","LiDFOB lower LUMO energy preferential decomposition","LiBO2 or Li2B4O7 higher Young's modulus than LiF","lower Li+ migration activation energy","EIS confirmation of effective SEI","reduced electrode expansion","LiTFSI corrosion of NCM811 as limitation"],"disallowed_extrapolations":["Claiming complete elimination of all degradation mechanisms","Attributing expansion suppression to electrolyte incombustibility","Generalizing cathode compatibility beyond NCM811 evidence"]}},"analysis":{"target_cognitive_object":"Full causal chain from solvation structure through SEI composition to mechanical and ionic transport properties, plus boundary limitation identification","primary_boundary":"Mechanistic chain must be grounded in reported coordination numbers, LUMO values, moduli, and activation energies; limitation must cite LiTFSI-NCM811 corrosion specifically","intended_error_modes":["omitting the LUMO-driven selectivity step","attributing SEI benefits solely to fluorination without boron-species specificity","ignoring cathode compatibility limitation"]}}]}
